The paper proposes a new active learning method for text classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). The paper focuses on selecting instances that most affect the embedding space, which is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of word embeddings, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions uncertainty sampling, which is a common approach in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, and cs.CV, in that order.
